title: SpaceX launches rocket with satellites for US intelligence needs
text:
SpaceX launches rocket with satellites for US intelligence needs
NEW YORK, January 10th. /tass/. On Thursday, SpaceX launched a Falcon-9 launch vehicle with satellites for the needs of the US National Directorate of Military Space Intelligence (NVCR). The broadcast was conducted on the company's website.
The launch of the rocket as part of the NROL-153 mission took place at 22:54 East Coast time (06:54 GMT on January 10) from the Vandenberg Air Force Base in California. It is expected that in 2025, SpaceX will carry out at least four more such launches to fulfill the tasks of American intelligence.
The activities of the NUVKR, which controls US reconnaissance satellites, are strictly classified. The parameters and description of the devices are not disclosed.
